Repository: https://github.com/warpXspeed/scalar-relaxation-cosmologyDear Colleagues,We present Scalar Relaxation Cosmology (SRC) not as a replacement for the Standard Model or General Relativity, but as a different foundational premise that may offer greater unity and fewer ad-hoc components.Core PremiseThe observable universe emerges from the dynamics of a single high-density scalar substrate field φ undergoing viscoelastic relaxation. All familiar phenomena — gravity, electromagnetism, particles, redshift, and structure formation — are different excitation modes and patterns within this one field.Key MechanismsGravity: Refractive density gradients (n ∝ ρ(φ)) + effective pressure from relaxation.  
Electromagnetism & Light: Piezoelectric shear modes (transverse waves) propagating through φ.  
Particles: Stable topological defects (vortices, skyrmions, dipoles) formed in φ.  
Redshift: Cumulative viscous damping (γ ∂_t φ) over distance — no metric expansion required.  
Memory & Quantum Effects: Hysteresis wakes left by defects.  
Intelligence: Emergent from sufficiently complex, interconnected wake networks.

Observational AnchorsWigner crystals (directly imaged 2024–2025): Electrons forming ordered lattices without atomic scaffolding — a direct signature of intrinsic ordering in the substrate.
Redshift: Naturally explained by damping rather than expansion.
Large-scale structure: Filaments and voids arise from propagating density pulses and wake patterns.
Black holes: Extreme high-ρ(φ) pinches with refractive cutoff boundaries (event horizons).

Comparison with Standard PhysicsSRC does not require non-baryonic dark matter, a separate dark energy component, or metric expansion. It derives these effects from the relaxation dynamics of one field. While it must ultimately be judged by its ability to reproduce observations and make novel predictions, its minimalist ontology offers a potential path to unification without extra dimensions or fine-tuning.We invite classical physicists to examine the framework on its own terms. Specific testable predictions include:Frequency-dependent anomalies in Wigner crystal lattice spacing and melting behavior.
Correlations between planetary/solar heat flux and galactic arm passages.
Subtle deviations in high-z redshift relations consistent with damping rather than expansion.

The full technical manual, simulations, and evolving predictions are available in the repository.We welcome constructive critique, calculations, and experimental ideas. If SRC’s mechanisms can be shown to be inconsistent with data, we will revise or abandon them. If they hold, they may provide a simpler foundation for understanding the universe.Thank you for your time and consideration.Gerald Henton
